'''Differdange communal council''' ({{lang-fr|Conseil communal de Differdange}}) is the [[Local government|local council]] for the [[Communes of Luxembourg|commune]] of [[Differdange]], in south-western [[Luxembourg]].
It consists of seventeen members, elected every six years by [[proportional representation]].<ref name="Conseil communal">{{cite web|url=http://www.differdange.lu/sujet/sujet.asp?sub=1,11 |title=Le Conseil communal de Differdange |accessdate=2007-09-06 |date= |publisher=Ville de Differdange |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071007064805/http://www.differdange.lu/sujet/sujet.asp?sub=1,11 |archivedate=2007-10-07 |language=fr |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> The last elections were held on 9 October 2005, and resulted in a victory for the [[Democratic Party (Luxembourg)|Democratic Party]] (DP). In the ''[[Collège échevinal (Luxembourg)|collège échevinal]]'', the DP forms a coalition with [[The Greens (Luxembourg)|The Greens]], who have the fourth-largest contingent, under the leadership of DP [[Mayor of Differdange|mayor]] [[Claude Meisch]].<ref name="Conseil communal" />
