'''E350''' is an [[European Union|EU]] recognised food additive. It comes in two forms,

:E350 (i) [[Monosodium malate]]
:E350 (ii) [[Disodium malate]]

[[Sodium malate]] is a [[salt|sodium salt]] of [[malic acid]] (E296), a natural acid present in fruit, its alate is used as a buffer and flavouring in [[soft drink]]s, [[confectionery]] and other foods.  The D,L - and D-[[isomers]] are not allowed for infants - who lack the enzymes to metabolise these compounds.

