{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2016}} {{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Ministry of Economy and Planning |type = Ministerial Department |logo = |logo_width = |logo_caption = |seal = |seal_width = |seal_caption = |formed = {{start date and age|2003}} |preceding1 =Central Planning Organization |preceding2 =Ministry of Planning |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction =[[Saudi Arabia]] |headquarters = [[Riyadh]] |employees = |budget = |minister1_name = [[Mohammed Altwejri]] |minister1_pfo = Minister |child1_agency = |child2_agency = |child3_agency = |website = [http://www.mep.gov.sa/themes/GoldenCarpet/index.jsp#1380264429308 Official website] |footnotes = }}
The '''Ministry of Economy and Planning''' ({{lang-ar|وزارة الاقتصاد والتخطيط}}) is one of the governmental bodies of [[Saudi Arabia]] and part of [[Cabinet of Saudi Arabia|the cabinet]]. The ministry has the function of developing and implementing five-year plans which reflect the long-term economical targets of the country.
==History== The ministry of economy was established in 1953.<ref name=stef>{{cite journal|author=Steffen Hertog|title=Shaping the Saudi state: Human agency's shifting role in the rentier state formation|url=http://dro.dur.ac.uk/4561/1/4561.pdf?DDD35+dgi4lh|journal=International Journal of Middle East Studies|year=2007|volume=39|pages=539–563|doi=10.1017/S0020743807071073|accessdate=4 January 2014}}</ref><ref name=gsa>{{cite journal|author1=Ghassane Salameh|author2=Vivian Steir|title=Political Power and the Saudi State|jstor=3010946|journal=MERIP Reports|date=October 1980|issue=91}}</ref> However, the body was not functional<ref name=stef/> and was disestablished in 1954.<ref name=gsa/>
The ministry of economy and planning was formed in 2003 when the ministry of planning and economy department were merged.<ref name=rad>{{cite web|title=Ministry of Planning and National Economy|url=http://www.saudinf.com/main/c6g.htm|work=SAMIRAD|accessdate=27 September 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Michael O'Kane|title=Doing Business in Saudi Arabia|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=f2UYn2z0iRAC&pg=PA21|accessdate=2 October 2014|date=March 2013|publisher=Michael OKane|isbn=978-0-615-43178-9|page=21}}</ref> Until 2003 the ministry of planning was in charge of development and implementation of five-year plans.<ref name=rad/><ref>{{cite journal|title=Arabic, Arabists and Academia|journal=Saudi Aramco World|date=May–June 1979|volume=30|issue=3|url=http://www.saudiaramcoworld.com/issue/197903/arabic.arabists.and.academia.htm|accessdate=11 October 2013}}</ref> The ministry is based in [[Riyadh]].<ref>[http://www.s-ge.com/de/filefield-private/files/2816/field_blog_public_files/4865 Basic addresses] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140224033210/http://www.s-ge.com/de/filefield-private/files/2816/field_blog_public_files/4865 |date=24 February 2014 }} ''OSCE''. September 2011. Retrieved 5 February 2014.</ref>
Since its foundation in 2003, the ministry has been headed by three ministers. The first minister was Khalid bin Mohammed Al Gosaibi who was appointed to the post in April 2003.<ref>{{cite web|title=Saudi Cabinet reshuffle|url=http://www.saudinf.com/display_news.php?id=539|work=SAMIRAD|accessdate=27 September 2013|location=Riyadh|date=30 April 2003}}</ref> [[Muhammed Al-Jasser|Mohammad Al Jasser]] was the minister of economy and planning from December 2011 to April 2015.<ref>{{cite news|title=Saudi Arabia’s King Appoints New Economic Team Amid Record Spending Plans|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-13/saudi-arabia-s-king-appoints-new-economic-team-amid-record-spending-plans.html|accessdate=27 September 2013|work=Bloomberg|date=13 December 2011|author=Glen Carey}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Profile-Saudi Economy and Planning Minister Muhammad Al Jasser|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2011/12/15/saudi-econmin-idUSL6E7NF1WJ20111215|accessdate=2 October 2014|work=Reuters|date=15 December 2011}}</ref> Adel Fakeih was appointed the minister of economy and planning in April 2015.
==Functions== The major function of the ministry is to prepare the [[development plan]]s of the country.<ref>{{cite web|title=Economy and Planning organizes the 10th development plan workshop|url=http://saudibiznews.com/business/item/1105-economy-and-planning-organizes-the-10th-development-plan-workshop|work=Saudi Business News|accessdate=2 October 2014}}</ref> It has various major agencies including the central department of statistics and the national computer center.<ref name=rad/><ref>{{cite web|title=System of General Statistics|url=http://www.cdsi.gov.sa/english/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=30&Itemid=29|work=Central Department of Statics and Information|accessdate=27 September 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130819003322/http://www.cdsi.gov.sa/english/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=30&Itemid=29|archivedate=19 August 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
